    "Secondly, alongside video recordings, physiological data of participants is most frequently used as a stimulus for SR research based on online platforms (10 articles).",
    "This trend is reasonable as screen recordings alone may not fully reflect students' behavior, mainly if they do not perform mouse manipulation or keyboard input.",
    "For instance, eye-gaze behaviors provide direct and objective evidence, including fixation duration, fixation count, and scanning path, allowing for stronger conclusions about learners' cognitive processes and learning strategies (Lai et al., 2013; Michel et al., 2020).",
    "Thirdly, the diagram indicates that studies utilizing SR in physical environments are more mature and inclined to utilize multimodal stimuli.",
    "However, studies in online platforms, OMO environments, and VR environments are still limited, with predominantly homogeneous stimuli."
